cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as Structure from Motion (SfM) and feature extraction using convolutional neural networks (CNN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves relocalization of keypoints, which falls under the category of robotics and automation (cs.RO). The use of CNN features for SfM reconstruction also involves machine learning techniques, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning models, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
